            <content type="html">
                
                &lt;iframe width=&#34;620&#34; height=&#34;360&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/9oXmg4s-Z8s&#34; frameborder=&#34;0&#34; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above is a visually enhanced scientific simulation of a tsunami wave &amp;#8220;hitting&amp;#8221; the harbor of Heraclion in Crete. The animation data were produced using a methodology for the photorealistic scientific visualization of tsunami waves, i&amp;#8217;ve been working on, with the Technical University of Crete, sporadically over the last 5 years. The video was presented, along with a scientific paper, at the &lt;span class=&#34;caps&#34;&gt;IEEE&lt;/span&gt; International Conference of Imaging Systems &lt;span class=&#34;amp&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; Techiques, last October in&amp;nbsp;Santorini.&lt;/p&gt;            </content>
